<DOC><DOCNO> AP900623-0013 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-06-23-90 0204EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-BRF--Egypt-Crash     06-23 0153</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BRF--Egypt-Crash,0157</SECOND><HEAD>Bus-Truck Crash Kills 22, Injures at Least 16</HEAD><DATELINE>CAIRO, Egypt (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A passenger bus carrying Moslem pilgrimsheading for Mecca collided with a truck, killing 22 people andinjuring at least 16, sources and newspaper reports said.   The truck crashed into the public bus carrying 60 people Fridayto Cairo's airport from Beni Suef, 75 miles south of the capital,the government-run Al-Ahram daily reported. It said 15 women wereamong the 22 dead.   A hospital source speaking on condition of anonymity said 16people were injured, while newspaper reports said as many as 25were hurt.   Al-Ahram said the truck driver sped away and police aresearching for him.   Newspapers said some of the passengers were to fly to SaudiArabia for the annual Moslem pilgrimage at Mecca which culminatesearly July. The rest were mostly family members of the pilgrimstraveling along to see their relatives off.</TEXT></DOC>